<p>A detailed, itemized proposal is fundamental for understanding your project's investment. It should clearly outline all costs, including materials, labor, and a clear payment schedule.<br/><br/>Always budget an additional 10-15% contingency fund for unforeseen issues, which are common, particularly in older Chicago homes. A trustworthy construction company will transparently explain how change orders—any modifications to the original scope—will be handled and priced upfront.</p>

